    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm looking at some expansion plans for my cafe in a smaller town where the cost of living isn't super high. I'm worried about the recent talks about raising the local minimum wage. Can you give me a breakdown of how these kinds of wage increases typically impact small businesses in areas like mine?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Wage increases, while beneficial for workers, directly increase your operational costs for your cafe. This forces you to either absorb the higher labor expenses, which cuts into your profit margins, or pass those costs on to your customers through higher menu prices. In a smaller town, price sensitivity can be higher, making this a significant balancing act for small businesses. You will need to carefully analyze your current pricing structure and projected sales volume to absorb the new minimum wage effectively.",
